nocide.org/ Combat Genocide Association website]\n* {{Citation | url = http://gsp.yale.edu/ | title = Genocide Studies Program | publisher = [[Yale University]]}}.\n* [http://www.trueactivist.com/when-you-kill-ten-million-africans-you-arent-called-hitler/ King Leopold II of Belgium]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Genocides In History}}\n[[Category:Genocides| ]]\n", "name_user": "OAO24", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genocides_in_history"}
{"title_page": "Michael Trulsen", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Michael Trulsen\n|image          = \n|fullname       = Michael Sandberg Trulsen\n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1989|12|28|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = forward\n|currentclub    = \n|youthyears1    = |youthclubs1 = [[Torp IF|Torp]]\n|youthyears2    = |youthclubs2 = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]\n|years1         = 2008\u20132009\n|clubs1         = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]] |caps1 = 8 |goals1 = 0\n|years2         = 2010\u20132011\n|clubs2         = [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]]\n|years3         = 2011\n|clubs3         = [[Nybergsund IL-Trysil|Nybergsund]]\n|years4         = 2012\n|clubs4         = [[\u00f8stsiden IL|\u00d8stsiden]]\n|years5         = 2014\u20132016\n|clubs5         = [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]]\n|club-update  = \n}}\n'''Michael Trulsen''' (born 28 December 1989) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] footballer who is playing as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]].\n\nHe started his senior career in [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]], appearing eight times in the [[Norwegian Premier League]] of 2008 and 2009. In 2010, he went on to neighbors [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]], who won promotion, and in 2011 he played seven first-tier games for them. He joined [[Nybergsund IL-Trysil|Nybergsund]] in mid-season.\n\nAfter the 2011 season he joined [[\u00d8stsiden IL]] in his hometown, but retired already in August 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Trulsen ga seg i \u00d8IL|date=11 August 2012|work=Demokraten|page=24|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He later made a comeback for lower-tier [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]].<ref>{{NFF|2125582}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Trulsen, Michael}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Fredrikstad]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Fredrikstad FK players]]\n[[Category:Sarpsborg 08 FF players]]\n[[Category:Nybergsund IL players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:1. divisjon players]]\n[[Category:\u00d8stsiden IL players]]\n[[Category:Lisleby FK players]]\n\n{{Norway-footy-forward-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Michael Trulsen\n|image          = \n|fullname       = Michael Sandberg Trulsen\n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1989|12|28|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = forward\n|currentclub    = \n|youthyears1    = |youthclubs1 = [[Torp IF|Torp]]\n|youthyears2    = |youthclubs2 = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]\n|years1         = 2008\u20132009\n|clubs1         = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]] |caps1 = 8 |goals1 = 0\n|years2         = 2010\u20132011\n|clubs2         = [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]]\n|years3         = 2011\n|clubs3         = [[Nybergsund IL-Trysil|Nybergsund]]\n|years4         = 2012\n|clubs4         = [[\u00f8stsiden IL|\u00d8stsiden]]\n|years5         = 2014\u20132016\n|clubs5         = [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]]\n|club-update  = \n}}\n'''Michael Trulsen''' (born 28 December 1989) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] footballer who is playing as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]].\n\nHe started his senior career in [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]], appearing eight times in the [[Norwegian Premier League]] of 2008 and 2009. In 2010, he went on to neighbors [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]], who won promotion, and in 2011 he played seven first-tier games for them. He joined [[Nybergsund IL-Trysil|Nybergsund]] in mid-season.\n\nAfter the 2011 season he joined [[\u00d8stsiden IL]] in his hometown, but retired already in August 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Trulsen ga seg i \u00d8IL|date=11 August 2012|work=Demokraten|page=24|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He later made a comeback for lower-tier [[Lisleby FK|Lisleby]].<ref>{{NFF|2125582}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Trulsen, Michael}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Fredrikstad]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Fredrikstad FK players]]\n[[Category:Sarpsborg 08 FF players]]\n[[Category:Nybergsund IL players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:1. divisjon players]]\n[[Category:\u00d8stsiden IL players]]\n[[Category:Lisleby FK players]]\n\n{{Norway-footy-forward-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Norwegian footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"Norwegian association football player\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Trulsen"}
{"title_page": "Erling Meirik", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian footballer and football executive}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Erling Meirik\n| image               = \n| fullname            = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1948|12|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Levanger]], [[Norway]]\n| height              = \n| currentclub         = \n| clubnumber          = \n| position            = [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1970\u201376\n| clubs1 = [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]]\n| caps1 = 123\n| goals1 = 13\n}}\n\n'''Erling Meirik''' (born 17 December 1948) is a Norwegian former football and football executive. Born in [[Levanger]], he played for [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]] between 1970 and 1976, being capped 134 times and scoring 14 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rbkmedia.no/statistikk/spiller.php?player_id=29 |title=Erling Meirik |publisher=Rosenborg BK |language=Norwegian |accessdate=20 July 2012}}</ref> He was Rosenborg's top scorer in the [[1970 Rosenborg BK season|1970 season]] with five goals.<ref name=top>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/distrikt/nrk_trondelag/1.5094796 |title=Toppscorere |publisher=[[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] |date=11 March 2010 |language=Norwegian |accessdate=15 April 2011 |archivedate=15 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5xxn4PI0q?url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/distrikt/nrk_trondelag/1.5094796 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was later hired as president of Rosenborg. He withdrew as president in 1983 as a consequence of the unsuccessful hiring of [[Tommy Cavanagh]] as manager.<ref name=s155>Svardal: 155</ref>\n\n==References==\n;Bibliography\n*{{cite book |title=Historien om Rosenborg Ballklubb 1917\u20132007 |last=Svardal |first=Geir |publisher=Tapir Akademosk Forlag |location=Trondheim |language=Norwegian |year=2007 |isbn=978-82-519-2188-6}}\n\n;Notes\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meirik, Erling}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Levanger]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Rosenborg BK players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:Rosenborg BK non-playing staff]]\n\n\n{{Norway-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Erling Meirik\n| image               = \n| fullname            = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1948|12|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Levanger]], [[Norway]]\n| height              = \n| currentclub         = \n| clubnumber          = \n| position            = [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1970\u201376\n| clubs1 = [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]]\n| caps1 = 123\n| goals1 = 13\n}}\n\n'''Erling Meirik''' (born 17 December 1948) is a Norwegian former football and football executive. Born in [[Levanger]], he played for [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]] between 1970 and 1976, being capped 134 times and scoring 14 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rbkmedia.no/statistikk/spiller.php?player_id=29 |title=Erling Meirik |publisher=Rosenborg BK |language=Norwegian |accessdate=20 July 2012}}</ref> He was Rosenborg's top scorer in the [[1970 Rosenborg BK season|1970 season]] with five goals.<ref name=top>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/distrikt/nrk_trondelag/1.5094796 |title=Toppscorere |publisher=[[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] |date=11 March 2010 |language=Norwegian |accessdate=15 April 2011 |archivedate=15 April 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5xxn4PI0q?url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/distrikt/nrk_trondelag/1.5094796 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was later hired as president of Rosenborg. He withdrew as president in 1983 as a consequence of the unsuccessful hiring of [[Tommy Cavanagh]] as manager.<ref name=s155>Svardal: 155</ref>\n\n==References==\n;Bibliography\n*{{cite book |title=Historien om Rosenborg Ballklubb 1917\u20132007 |last=Svardal |first=Geir |publisher=Tapir Akademosk Forlag |location=Trondheim |language=Norwegian |year=2007 |isbn=978-82-519-2188-6}}\n\n;Notes\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meirik, Erling}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Levanger]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Rosenborg BK players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:Rosenborg BK non-playing staff]]\n\n\n{{Norway-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Norwegian footballer and football executive\", overriding Wikidata description \"Norwegian footballer\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erling_Meirik"}
{"title_page": "Tequila (Jax Jones, Martin Solveig and Raye song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 single by Jax Jones, Martin Solveig and Raye}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Tequila\n| cover      = Jax Jones - Tequila.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jax Jones]], [[Martin Solveig]] and [[Raye (singer)|Raye]]\n| album      = Europa\n| released   = {{start date|2020|2|21|df=y}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=30}}\n| label      = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Jax Jones|Timucin Aluo]]|[[Martin Solveig]]|[[Mark Ralph (record producer)|Mark Ralph]]|[[MNEK|Uzoechi Emenike]]|[[Raye (singer)|Rachel Keen]]|[[Jin Jin (musician)|Janee Bennett]]|Jamie Spinks}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Jax Jones]]|Alex Tepper ({{abbr|add.|Additional production}})|Ralph (add.)|Solveig (add.)}}\n| chronology = [[Jax Jones]]\n| prev_title = [[This Is Real]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Martin Solveig]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Juliet & Romeo]]\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Tequila\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Raye (singer)|Raye]] singles\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = All of My Love\n | prev_year  = 2020\n | title      = Tequila\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Tequila'''\" is a song by British DJ [[Jax Jones]], French DJ [[Martin Solveig]] and British singer [[Raye (singer)|Raye]], released as a single on 21 February 2020. It will be included in Jones' and Solveig's upcoming ''Europa'' project.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiowebitalia.it/140935/in-news/jax-jones-martin-solveig-e-raye-con-tequila-dal-21-febbraio.html|title=Jax Jones, Martin Solveig e Raye con \"Tequila\" dal 21 febbraio|website=Radio Web Italia|language=it|date=20 February 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> While this marks the first time Solveig and Raye collaborated, it is the second time Jones and Raye, as well as Jones and Solveig worked together, on \"[[You Don't Know Me (Jax Jones song)|You Don't Know Me]]\" and \"[[All Day and Night]]\", respectively.\n\n==Background==\nJones first introduced the song at the Brooklyn nightclub \"Elsewhere\" on 20 April 2019. The song was then described as \"characteristically bass-heavy\" and \"uptempo\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earlybirdnyc.com/2019/04/21/watch-jax-jones-reveals-unreleased-song-tequila-ft-raye-at-elsewhere/|title=Watch: Jax Jones Reveals Unreleased Song \"Tequila\" Ft. Raye at Elsewhere|website=earlybirdnyc.com|date=21 April 2019|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> During an interview on 23 January 2020, Raye revealed that the song would be out soon and that it is the \"only other record\" her and Jones had written together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/hits-radio/entertainment/music/raye-jax-jones-tequila/|title=RAYE spills the tea on a VERY exciting Jax Jones collab coming soon \ud83d\ude4c|last=Sky Hulton|first=Anna|website=planetradio.co.uk|date=23 January 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> On 4 February 2020, Jones posted a clip of himself preparing a meal in the kitchen with a snippet of the song playing as he opens a pot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shiningbeats.pl/europa-tequila-teaser/|title=Martin Solveig i Jax Jones wracaj\u0105 do projektu Europa! Czy \"Tequila\" powt\u00f3rzy sukces \"All Day And Night\"?|last=Brodowski|first=Krzysztof|website=shiningbeats.pl|language=pl|date=19 February 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> He went on to post a clip of the trio at the video set in front of a green screen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JaxJones/status/1230190719295422465|title=WHAT YOU KNOW: Tequila \ud83c\udf79 is out friday, the video is out friday, issa banger \ud83c\udf89 WHAT YOU DIDNT KNOW: in the video i debut my incredible hair line regrowth \ud83e\udd20, im now grade 8 saxophone \ud83c\udfb7, raye is about to become a sex symbol cos of the vid \ud83d\udc83 @martinsolveig @raye|via=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Cover art==\nThe cover was revealed on 17 February 2020 and shows a red [[BMW M3#E30 generation (1986\u20131991)|BMW E30 M3]] with stereotypical Mexican illustrations in the background.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JaxJones/status/1229468745866850306|title=I said TEQUILA IS COMING!! THIS FRIDAY cc @martinsolveig @raye|via=Twitter|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|23|date=20200417|rowheader=true|accessdate=18 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4826|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=2 March 2020|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n| 32\n|-\n{{single chart|Russia|66|rowheader=true|date=2020-03-13|accessdate=21 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|19|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|31|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddanceelectronic|39|artist=Jax Jones|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 March 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Jax Jones}}\n{{Martin Solveig}}\n{{Raye (singer)}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Jax Jones songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jax Jones]]\n[[Category:Martin Solveig songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 single by Jax Jones, Martin Solveig and Raye}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Tequila\n| cover      = Jax Jones - Tequila.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jax Jones]], [[Martin Solveig]] and [[Raye (singer)|Raye]]\n| album      = Europa\n| released   = {{start date|2020|2|21|df=y}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=30}}\n| label      = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Jax Jones|Timucin Aluo]]|[[Martin Solveig]]|[[Mark Ralph (record producer)|Mark Ralph]]|[[MNEK|Uzoechi Emenike]]|[[Raye (singer)|Rachel Keen]]|[[Jin Jin (musician)|Janee Bennett]]|Jamie Spinks}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Jax Jones]]|Alex Tepper ({{abbr|add.|Additional production}})|Ralph (add.)|Solveig (add.)}}\n| chronology = [[Jax Jones]]\n| prev_title = [[This Is Real]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Martin Solveig]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Juliet & Romeo]]\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Tequila\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Raye (singer)|Raye]] singles\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = All of My Love\n | prev_year  = 2020\n | title      = Tequila\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Tequila'''\" is a song by British DJ [[Jax Jones]], French DJ [[Martin Solveig]] and British singer [[Raye (singer)|Raye]], released as a single on 21 February 2020. It will be included in Jones' and Solveig's upcoming ''Europa'' project.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiowebitalia.it/140935/in-news/jax-jones-martin-solveig-e-raye-con-tequila-dal-21-febbraio.html|title=Jax Jones, Martin Solveig e Raye con \"Tequila\" dal 21 febbraio|website=Radio Web Italia|language=it|date=20 February 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> While this marks the first time Solveig and Raye collaborated, it is the second time Jones and Raye, as well as Jones and Solveig worked together, on \"[[You Don't Know Me (Jax Jones song)|You Don't Know Me]]\" and \"[[All Day and Night]]\", respectively.\n\n==Background==\nJones first introduced the song at the Brooklyn nightclub \"Elsewhere\" on 20 April 2019. The song was then described as \"characteristically bass-heavy\" and \"uptempo\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earlybirdnyc.com/2019/04/21/watch-jax-jones-reveals-unreleased-song-tequila-ft-raye-at-elsewhere/|title=Watch: Jax Jones Reveals Unreleased Song \"Tequila\" Ft. Raye at Elsewhere|website=earlybirdnyc.com|date=21 April 2019|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> During an interview on 23 January 2020, Raye revealed that the song would be out soon and that it is the \"only other record\" her and Jones had written together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/hits-radio/entertainment/music/raye-jax-jones-tequila/|title=RAYE spills the tea on a VERY exciting Jax Jones collab coming soon \ud83d\ude4c|last=Sky Hulton|first=Anna|website=planetradio.co.uk|date=23 January 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> On 4 February 2020, Jones posted a clip of himself preparing a meal in the kitchen with a snippet of the song playing as he opens a pot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shiningbeats.pl/europa-tequila-teaser/|title=Martin Solveig i Jax Jones wracaj\u0105 do projektu Europa! Czy \"Tequila\" powt\u00f3rzy sukces \"All Day And Night\"?|last=Brodowski|first=Krzysztof|website=shiningbeats.pl|language=pl|date=19 February 2020|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> He went on to post a clip of the trio at the video set in front of a green screen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JaxJones/status/1230190719295422465|title=WHAT YOU KNOW: Tequila \ud83c\udf79 is out friday, the video is out friday, issa banger \ud83c\udf89 WHAT YOU DIDNT KNOW: in the video i debut my incredible hair line regrowth \ud83e\udd20, im now grade 8 saxophone \ud83c\udfb7, raye is about to become a sex symbol cos of the vid \ud83d\udc83 @martinsolveig @raye|via=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Cover art==\nThe cover was revealed on 17 February 2020 and shows a red [[BMW M3#E30 generation (1986\u20131991)|BMW E30 M3]] with stereotypical Mexican illustrations in the background.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JaxJones/status/1229468745866850306|title=I said TEQUILA IS COMING!! THIS FRIDAY cc @martinsolveig @raye|via=Twitter|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|44|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=11 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4826|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=2 March 2020|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n| 32\n|-\n{{single chart|Russia|66|rowheader=true|date=2020-03-13|accessdate=21 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|19|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|31|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddanceelectronic|39|artist=Jax Jones|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 March 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Jax Jones}}\n{{Martin Solveig}}\n{{Raye (singer)}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Jax Jones songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jax Jones]]\n[[Category:Martin Solveig songs]]\n", "name_user": "Ss112", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCharts:updated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tequila_(Jax_Jones,_Martin_Solveig_and_Raye_song)"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Singapore}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore\n| map1            = COVID-19 Cases in Singapore by Planning Areas.svg\n| legend1         = {{center|Map of planning areas with confirmed (red) coronavirus cases (as of 16 April)}}\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Singapore]]\n| first_case      = 23 January 2020\n| arrival_date    = 23 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| recovery_cases  = 708<ref name=\"worldometers\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ |title=worldometers.info |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129195657/https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ |archive-date=29 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| deaths          = 10<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\">{{Cite web |url=https://coronaboard.com/ |title=COVID-19 Dashboard |access-date=5 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331135805/https://coronaboard.com/ |archive-date=31 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 5,050<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.coronatracker.com/country/sg |title=Corona Tracker Overview |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325143811/https://www.coronatracker.com/country/sg/ |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>|Action taken: Circuit Breaker (7 Apr-4 May 2020)\nStatus: Enforcing (Expires: 4 May 2020; Tentative)\n| active          = \n| suspected_cases = 25 000\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{url|https://www.moh.gov.sg/covid-19}}\n| First Case detected: = \n| Deaths from other causes = \n| Death from other causes = 1\n}}\nThe '''2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore''' is part of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing global pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2).\n\nThe first case of COVID-19 was confirmed on 23 January.<ref name=\"Abdullah 2020\" /> To combat COVID-19, a multi-ministerial committee was formed on 22 January with Minister for National Development [[Lawrence Wong]] and Minister for Health [[Gan Kim Yong]] as the co-chairs and [[Prime Minister of Singapore|Prime Minister]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] and [[Deputy Prime Minister of Singapore|Deputy Prime Minister]] and Minister for Finance [[Heng Swee Keat]] as advisors.<ref name=\"ST22Jan\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/default-document-library/multi-ministry-taskforce-on-wuhan-coronavirus-and-tor---final.pdf |title=Multi-Ministry Taskforce on Wuhan Coronavirus:  Terms of Reference (TORs) and Composition |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321054236/https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/default-document-library/multi-ministry-taskforce-on-wuhan-coronavirus-and-tor---final.pdf |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, Singapore announced a stringent set of preventive measures which were collectively called a 'circuit breaker'. This will be applied from 7 April to 4 May 2020.\n[[Singapore]] contributed US$500,000 to support [[WHO]] efforts against COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |title=Singapore contributes US$500,000 to support WHO efforts against COVID-19 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-contributes-s-500-000-to-support-who-covid-19-efforts-12568566 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=CNA |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325020159/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-contributes-s-500-000-to-support-who-covid-19-efforts-12568566 |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Singapore medical cases chart}}\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Statistics ==\nThe top plot shows the total number of cases as a function of time (by date) since 23 January 2020, the date of the first reported case in Singapore. The bottom plot shows the number of new cases as reported each day.\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|colors=Orange, OrangeRed, Blue, Red\n| legend=Legend\n| width = 900\n| height = 400\n| xAxisTitle = Date (day/month)\n| yAxisTitle = Total no. of cases (cumulative)\n| y1Title=Confirmed\n| y2Title=Active\n| y3Title=Recovered\n| y4Title=Deaths\n| xAxisAngle = -65\n| yGrid= |xGrid= \n| x =  23/1, 24/1, 25/1, 26/1, 27/1, 28/1, 29/1, 30/1, 31/1, 1/2, 2/2, 3/2, 4/2, 5/2, 6/2, 7/2, 8/2, 9/2, 10/2, 11/2, 12/2, 13/2, 14/2, 15/2, 16/2, 17/2, 18/2, 19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23/2, 24/2, 25/2, 26/2, 27/2, 28/2, 29/2, 1/3, 2/3, 3/3, 4/3, 5/3, 6/3, 7/3, 8/3, 9/3, 10/3, 11/3, 12/3, 13/3, 14/3, 15/3, 16/3, 17/3, 18/3, 19/3, 20/3, 21/3, 22/3, 23/3, 24/3, 25/3, 26/3, 27/3, 28/3, 29/3, 30/3, 31/3, 1/4, 2/4