03bf\u03c3\u03c0\u03ac\u03b8\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1\u03c1\u03c7\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u039a\u03b1\u03c5\u03ba\u03ac\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c4\u03bf 1917 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bb\u03cc\u03b3\u03bf\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2|trans-title=The attempt to raise the Greek Caucasus Division and the reasons for its failure|language=Greek |url=http://histsociety.web.auth.gr/praktika-2009.pdf|journal=1st Panhellenic History Congress|volume=1|issue=1|pages=227\u2013251|issn=|accessdate=8 May 2018}}\n*{{cite book|title=Ottoman Greeks in the age of nationalism: Politics, Economy and Society in the Nineteenth Century|first=Alexis|last=Alexandris|year=1999|chapter=The Greek census of Anatolia and Thrace (1910\u20131912): a contribution to Ottoman Historical Demography|publisher=Darwin|location=Princeton, N.J.|editor1-first=Dimitri|editor1-last=Gondicas|editor2-first=Charles|editor2-last=Issawi|pages=45\u201376|ref=harv}}\n*[[Neal Ascherson|Ascherson, Neal]] (1995). ''Black Sea'', New York: Hill and Wang, {{ISBN|0-8090-3043-8}}.\n*{{Citation | url = http://www.armenica.org/material/master_thesis_vahagn_avedian.pdf | last = Avedian | first = Vahagn | title = The Armenian Genocide 1915: From a Neutral Small State's Perspective: Sweden | type = unpublished master thesis paper | publisher = Uppsala University | year = 2009}}.\n*Bassiouni, M. Cherif (1999). ''Crimes Against Humanity in International Criminal Law'', The Hague: Kluwer, ISBN *Hulse, Carl (2007). ''[https://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/26/washington/26cong.html?_r=1&adxnnl=1&ref=todayspaper&adxnnlx=1218637709-3ZKHw2PW5e7+L2WSj2ViLg&oref=slogin U.S. and Turkey Thwart Armenian Genocide Bill]'', The New York Times, 26 October 2007\n*{{citation| last = Bierstadt | first = Edward Hale | year = 1924 | title = The Great Betrayal; A Survey of the Near East Problem | place = New York | publisher = RM McBride & Co}}.\n*{{Citation | last = Bloxham | first = Donald | year = 2005 | title = The Great Game of Genocide: Imperialism, Nationalism, and the Destruction of the Ottoman Armenians | place = Oxford | publisher = Oxford University Press}}.\n*{{Citation | last = Ferguson | first = Niall | author-link = Niall Ferguson | year = 2006 | title = The War of the World: Twentieth-century Conflict And the Descent of the West | place = New York | publisher = Penguin | isbn = 978-1-59420-100-4 | url = https://archive.org/details/warofworldtwenti00nial }}.\n*{{Citation | last = Fotiadis | first = Constantinos Emm | year = 2004 | title = The Genocide of the Pontus Greeks by the Turks | volume = 13, 14| place = Thessaloniki | publisher = Herodotus}}.\n*{{Citation | author-link=Isabel V. Hull | last = Hull | first = Isabel V | year = 2005 | title = Absolute Destruction: Military Culture and the Practices of War in Imperial Germany | place = Ithaca | publisher = Cornell University Press}}.\n*{{Citation | last = Jones | first = Adam | title = Genocide: A Comprehensive Introduction | publisher = Routledge |year=2006}}.\n*{{Citation | last = Jones | first = Adam | title = Genocide: A Comprehensive Introduction | publisher = Taylor & Francis |year=2010 | origyear = 2006 |isbn= 978-0-415-48618-7 | author-mask = 3}}.\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Klapsis | first1 = Antonis | year = 2014 | title = Violent Uprooting and Forced Migration: A Demographic Analysis of the Greek Populations of Asia Minor, Pontus and Eastern Thrace | url = | journal = Middle Eastern Studies | volume = 50 | issue = 4| pages = 622\u2013639 | doi = 10.1080/00263206.2014.901218 }}\n*{{cite book|title=\u03a0\u03cc\u03bb\u03b5\u03bc\u03bf\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03ba\u03ac\u03b8\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03b7: \u0397 \u03be\u03b5\u03c7\u03b1\u03c3\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b7 \u03c0\u03bb\u03b5\u03c5\u03c1\u03ac \u03bc\u03b9\u03b1\u03c2 \u