{"title_page": "\u00d8ivind Holmsen", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian footballer}}\n{{More citations needed|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name=\u00d8ivind Holmsen\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=\u00d8ivind Holmsen\n|birth_date={{Birth date|1912|4|28}}\n|birth_place=[[Norway]]\n|death_date={{Death date and age|1996|8|23|1912|4|28}}\n|death_place =\n|height=\n|position=[[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|years1=|clubs1=|caps1=|goals1=\n|totalcaps=|totalgoals=\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=[[Norway national football team|Norway]]|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n}}\n{{MedalTop}}\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Football]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1936 Summer Olympics|1936 Berlin]] |[[Football at the 1936 Summer Olympics|Team]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''\u00d8ivind Holmsen''' (28 April 1912 in [[Oslo]] \u2013 23 August 1996) was a [[Norwegia]]n [[Norway national football team|international]] footballer. He played left back for [[F.C. Lyn Oslo|Lyn]] and the [[1936 Summer Olympics|1936 Olympic]] bronze team. He also played in the [[1938 FIFA World Cup]], and got 36 caps in total.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.home.no/greenriver/players/holmsen.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728195459/http://www.home.no/greenriver/players/holmsen.html |archive-date=28 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{NFF}}\n\n{{Norway Squad 1936 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Norway Squad 1938 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holmsen, Oivind}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:1996 deaths]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Norway international footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1936 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Norway]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Norway]]\n[[Category:1938 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Lyn Fotball players]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1936 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{Norway-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{norway-footy-defender-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name=\u00d8ivind Holmsen\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=\u00d8ivind Holmsen\n|birth_date={{Birth date|1912|4|28}}\n|birth_place=[[Norway]]\n|death_date={{Death date and age|1996|8|23|1912|4|28}}\n|death_place =\n|height=\n|position=[[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|years1=|clubs1=|caps1=|goals1=\n|totalcaps=|totalgoals=\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=[[Norway national football team|Norway]]|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n}}\n{{MedalTop}}\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Football]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1936 Summer Olympics|1936 Berlin]] |[[Football at the 1936 Summer Olympics|Team]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''\u00d8ivind Holmsen''' (28 April 1912 in [[Oslo]] \u2013 23 August 1996) was a [[Norwegia]]n [[Norway national football team|international]] footballer. He played left back for [[F.C. Lyn Oslo|Lyn]] and the [[1936 Summer Olympics|1936 Olympic]] bronze team. He also played in the [[1938 FIFA World Cup]], and got 36 caps in total.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.home.no/greenriver/players/holmsen.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120728195459/http://www.home.no/greenriver/players/holmsen.html |archive-date=28 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{NFF}}\n\n{{Norway Squad 1936 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Norway Squad 1938 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holmsen, Oivind}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:1996 deaths]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:No